“I also do not believe that if this had happened, it would have an impact on the autonomy of the regulatory authority” and recalled that planning public policy in strategic areas, such as the telecommunications sector, had a bearing on the federal executive authority, which had a constitutional mandate, was the management of the State.
Replacing analog signals to digital - one of the most important changes in recent years - has led to better use of the radio spectrum, better quality of the signal and more channels.
Postponing the transition, he said, would mean delaying the benefits of digital transformation, which includes meeting the public needs, which have not only a technical dimension, “as it covers economic, social, political and national security issues”.
